HR Officer - PT Amway Indonesia
HR Officer  -
HR Officer
Responsibilities
Assist the Talent Development Manager in talent development, performance management and workforce planningCoordinate the implementation of development programsArrange training courses with relevant personnel including inviting attendees, ensuring room set-up is complete and obtaining evaluation feedback from participantsCoordinate and oversee the administration of new and existing employees undertaking relevant development programsSource relevant external training, training providers, or training solutions based on the annual training planSupport performance management implementation by monitoring appraisal and interim review documentation in a timely fashion, chase outstanding forms and review all appraisals for consistencyCoordinate Employee Events and social media (Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, etc)Any other duties relevant to the position as delegated by the Talent Development Manager or Head of HR. Requirements:A Bachelor's DegreeRequired skills: analytical, planning, interpersonal communications, people handling and motivation.Must have English fluency in writing, speaking and listeningAt least 1 year working experience Competencies:Good analytical and planning skillsStrong communication and interpersonal skillsTactful and discrete when dealing with people and confidential informationProficient in MS Office and Social MediaWilling to travel  APPLY NOW OR SEND YOUR COMPLETE CV WITH CERTIFICATES/DEGREE & PHOTO TO: hrd@amway.co.idSubject Title: HR Officer  Only qualified candidates will be contacted. Thank you for your time and interest in Amway Indonesia.
